IS THERE A LIVE SUPPORT?
I'm here to help with whatever you need! Let me know your question, and I'll do my best to assist you right away.
I WANT TO KNOW ABOUT THE METRICS FOR DROPSHIPPING PRODUCTS

Sure, I can help with that! Could you please specify which metrics you're interested in for your dropshipping products? For example, are you looking for information on conversion rates, click-through rates, or something else?
YES THAT IS WHAT AM LOOKING FOR

Great! On NewsBreak, you can track various metrics for your dropshipping products, including CPM (Cost Per Thousand Impressions), clicks, CTR (Click-Through Rate), CPC (Cost Per Click), and CVR (Conversion Rate). You can view these metrics on your dashboard and filter the date range within the past 30 days. For more detailed information, please refer to our Ads Overview document.
HOW DO I KNOW WHEN I GET A PURCHISE

To track purchases, you can use the 'Conversions' metric in your reporting section. This metric will show you the number of desired actions completed by users after interacting with your ad, such as a purchase. You can also set up postback tracking to get real-time updates on conversions. For more details on setting up postback tracking, please refer to this article: [How to integrate a Newsbreak Postback with CPV One](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/34188623183757-How-to-integrate-a-Newsbreak-Postback-with-CPV-One).
WHAT THE COLOR RED SIGNIFY

The color red can signify various things depending on the context. In general, red is often associated with urgency, importance, or alertness. In advertising metrics, it might be used to highlight areas that need attention or improvement. If you see red in your dashboard or reports, it could indicate a metric that is underperforming or requires immediate action.
WHAT COLOR THE PIXEL SHOULD HAVE

The color of the pixel itself doesn't matter for tracking purposes. Pixels are typically invisible on your website and are used to track user actions. If you need help with installing a NewsBreak Pixel, you can refer to this article: [How to install a NewsBreak Pixel with GTM](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/14333966189581-How-to-install-a-NewsBreak-Pixel-with-GTM).
WHAT TYPE OF PRODUCT DO THIS FLATFORM ADVERTISE IS IT PRINT ON DEMAND OR DROPSHIPING PHYSICAL PRODUCTS

NewsBreak allows you to advertise a variety of products, including both print-on-demand and dropshipping physical products. You can create ad campaigns tailored to your specific product type and track their performance using our Ad Manager tools.
HOW DO I KNOW THAT ADDS ARE OK

To ensure your ads are compliant and performing well, you can check the status of your ads in the Ad Manager dashboard. If your ads are pending due to a new account not being verified, please provide the following details by emailing adsupport@newsbreak.com with the subject line: Business Verification –
- Company's full address
- Company's legal entity name
- Company's EHID or DUNS number
- Primary contact person's name
- Company's phone number
Once we receive this information, we will conduct a thorough review and update you on your account status. We appreciate your cooperation in maintaining a secure and compliant advertising environment for all our partners.
WHAT IS EHID AND DUNS NUMBER

EHID stands for Employer Identification Number, which is a unique identifier assigned to businesses by the IRS for tax purposes. DUNS number stands for Data Universal Numbering System, which is a unique nine-digit identifier for businesses provided by Dun & Bradstreet. Both numbers are used to verify the identity and legitimacy of a business.
DO I GET EMAIL WHEN GET A PURCHISE

Typically, you won't receive an email notification for each purchase directly from NewsBreak. However, you can set up postback tracking or integrate with third-party tools to get real-time updates and notifications for purchases. For more details on setting up postback tracking, please refer to this article: [How to integrate a Newsbreak Postback with CPV One](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/34188623183757-How-to-integrate-a-Newsbreak-Postback-with-CPV-One).
THANK YOU
You're welcome! If you have any more questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask. Have a great day!
HELLO HOW DO I ADD ADD CREDIT

Hi! To add ad credits to your NewsBreak account, follow these steps:
1. Log in to your NewsBreak Ad Manager account.
2. Navigate to the 'Billing' section.
3. Choose the 'Add Funds' option.
4. Select your preferred payment method (Autopay or Prepay).
5. Enter the amount you wish to add and complete the payment process.
For more detailed information, you can refer to our Billing Guide: [Billing Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17821681919757-Billing-Guide).
